EDITORS COMMENTS

Great moment captured in this print as Jack Wilshere of Arsenal Football Club shines during the Emirates Cup Pre-Season match against AC Milan at Emirates Stadium on July 31, 2010. The score was 1-1, with both teams showcasing their skills and determination in the lead up to the new Premier League season. Jack Wilshere, then a young and promising midfielder for Arsenal, was making a name for himself with his impressive performances on the pitch. In this game, he demonstrated his exceptional ball control, vision, and passing abilities, leaving the AC Milan defenders in his wake. The Emirates Cup Pre-Season tournament is an annual event that brings together top football clubs from around the world to compete in a series of friendly matches at Emirates Stadium. This particular match against AC Milan was a highly anticipated one, with both teams boasting strong squads and a history of exciting encounters. The photo captures Jack Wilshere in the midst of the action, focused intently on the ball as he prepares to make a pass. The crowd roars in the background, adding to the electric atmosphere of the stadium. The image is a testament to the passion and energy that surrounds football, as well as the talent and skill of the players on display. This print is a treasured memento for any Arsenal fan, offering a glimpse into the past and a reminder of the exciting moments that have shaped the history of the club. It is a reminder of Jack Wilshere's potential and the impact he had on the team during the 2010-2011 season. Credit for this photo goes to David Price of Arsenal Football Club, who captured this moment perfectly and preserved it for future generations of Arsenal fans to enjoy.
